com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.jsom.api
Interface VariableDeclarator

All Superinterfaces:
JSOM
public interface VariableDeclarator
extends JSOM

This JSOM type represents a variable declarator.

A variable declarator contains the variable identifier and optionally a variable initializer. This class also represents declarators for constants (i.e. variables with the modifier final within the modifier list). For some constant declarators the variable initializer is not optional, i.e. it must exist (field declarations within interface declarations), but ensuring this is up to a parser or whatever.

Author:
Dieter Habelitz
